messages "emerald\n**\nTo: mangla\nSubj: wands\nDate: Dec  3\n\nok, there's a whole mess o' wands in this stuff to recode, inheriting from a wand file that was originally created by ted.\nshall i keep it that way, recreating the inheritable wand file in my dir,\nor do you powers-that-be want to concoct a std_wand obj or some such?\nor is there one out there that i missed when i went looking for it.\neagerly anticipating your sage advice\n-E\n\n**\ntexas\n**\nTo: mangla\nSubj: Restoration of a character \nCc: arches, texas\nDate: Mar 21\n\nHi folks.  This is the real Texas mailiong you all.  I have been away for a while due to a lack of access which has now been rectified.  Could you please restore my wiz char for me and mail me.  Mail me anyway (those who remember me), even if you cant restore the char.\n\nThe email address is as follows :\n\nTexas@lineone.net\n\n\nTa muchly folks.\n\n\n\n\nTex.\n\n**\nsauron\n**\nTo: mangla\nFwd:  possible new ability for players\nDate: Apr 21\n\nTo: sauron\nSubj: possible new ability for players\nCc: haplo\nDate: Apr 20\n\nhave a look at ~texas/master.c and shield.c\n\nOrigonally coded them for the adventurers guild, but you might\nfind they fit better in another guild, not sure.\n\nIts designed to actively support team playing by allowing one person\nto increase the ac of several others for a short period of time.\n\nlet us know what ya think\n\nTex.\n\n**\nsauron\n**\nTo: mangla\nSubj: Areas for QC\nDate: Apr 25\n\nOk here's a brief list...\n\nBlaarg: No idea on theme. Was told start room is \n        '/players/blaarg/area/rooms/entry.c'.\n\nBobo: Red-rock in '/players/bobo/krooms/vill/'.\n\nIishima: Think he's ready. Assume area is in '/players/iishima/area/'.\n\nShadowmonk: Not sure if he's 100% ready, but some feedback might spur him\n            on. Assume area is in '/players/shadowmonk/area1/'.\n\nTexas: A small newbie forest (I think) in '/players/texas/forest/'.\n\nThat should be enough to keep you going for a while. :)\n\nDave\n\n**\nsauron\n**\nTo: mangla\nSubj: Package\nDate: Jun  5\n\nA rather large box of stuff arrived yesterday evening and I just HAD to say\nTHANX! :D I wasn't expecting quite so much stuff... After a hectic week,\nclass is slowing down again - COBOL doesn't seem to be a difficult\nlanguage to understand... just very wordy. It's as boring as I expected\nit to be. ;) How long do you think it will be before you need some of the\nstuff you sent over? I wish I could get my hands on a CD burner - even after\ncompressing my dos partition I don't have all that much HD space to spare.\nOh for a job (and hence some money)!\n\nAnything exciting happened on the mud while I've been absent? The boards\nseem as quiet as ever. I'm still working on quite a few things, and I\nstill haven't heard anything from James - I'll try writing to him again\nthis weekend and see if I get a responce. Just getting my hands on whatever\nhe's done up til now would be good.\n\nI've got to get going for now - got to get ready for class - but I hope to\nbe around more this weekend so we should bump into each other at some point.\nThanx again for the stuff - I can see that I've got alot of reading ahead\nof me!\n\nDave\n\n**\nwilbie\n**\nTo: mangla\nSubj: access to ninja\nCc: warlord,sauron\nDate: Jun 30\n\nCould I get access to Patience's directory (at least the ones for ninja).\nI am testing out some ninja weapons and need to inherit some of the files.\n\nTanx.\n\n**\nsypher\n**\nTo: mangla\nSubj: playerkilling\nDate: Jul  6\n\nmangla-\ntop 3 reasons for killing fritz:\n1) he stole from me,\n2) he snared, mudballed, and attacked me,\n3) he repeatedly did the same to alexg... a newbie and a friend of mine.\n\nwhile killing him for alexg is not a valid reason, his stealing\nand attacking me is (at least in my mind)....\nI know playerkilling is illegal now, but i think that the old rules of pk-ing\nshould apply.\n\nif I am mistaken, please let me know.\n\n   sypher\n\n**\nquilt\n**\nTo: mangla\nSubj: thieves\nCc: blade,brainsprain,septian\nDate: Jul 30\n\nok i basically am gonna compare thieves and monks (cos you guys already wiped out the other guilds)\nmonks can hide in dark - why?\nmonks have death blows..fine..they can use them as many times as they want..thieves only get one backstab\ndeath blow does 2/3 damage of backstab i suppose\nmonks have HEAPS of other combat abilities\nadmittedly..some of those abilities are shit..but when you consider that we only have one\ndoesn't seem to make sense\n\nnow i'm not trying to take down monks...(although they are overpowered) but thieves are now too underpowered without ambush or throw..\nnow they were buggy (or so blade told me)..fair enough..but surely we can get something to complement backstab\n\nand i think also that most of the thief abilities are pk orientated..because to put it simply they are relevant to most npcs who a)have more hp and b)are not effected by mudballs and stuff\n\nanyway..i had a few suggestions in the past..i'll mail them to you if you like..\n\nP.S. we don't want to powerup backstab..just want some combat options\n\n**\nwilbie\n**\nTo: mangla\nSubj: Sheankala\nDate: Jul 31\n\nSheankala has a death shout that contains the name and guild of the player\nwho kills her.  She shouts \"someone\" when the player is invisible.  I was\noriginally told (May have been Sauron but I forget) not to bother fixing\nthis because it would be \"giving away the identity of an invisible player\"...\n\nActually, I was thinking of making the room she's in no_invis (she is a god\nafter all) and this should clear it up.  Any suggestions?\n\n**\ncoan\n**\nTo: mangla\nSubj: I forgot my password to my character\nDate: Aug  3\n\nHi there, \nI forgot the password to my character.\nCharacter Name: Scan\n\nCan you please help me with this matter!\nThanks\n@\n\n**\nleeloo\n**\nTo: mangla\nSubj: sorry\nDate: Sep  1\n\noh im sorry\ni was drunk and didnt understand the concept\nlove\nleeloo\n\n**\nakira\n**\nTo: mangla\nSubj: barbarians\nDate: Sep  1\n\nA long time ago you told me to try to fix the barbs. Well I\nfailed. The code needs the skills program that use to be in\nthe code of the old barb guild and I could no get around it.\nSo I coded some new powers that you could use instead but I\nneed your help to get them to work. Look in /p/a/psi/bin and\nlook at nosebreak and summon and rage. Summon rage will take\nthe place of barbarian combat once I or you get it to work\nand nosebreak will be a high level hold. The summon rage needs\na lot of work I would like it to be like a haste and strength\nspell roled into one for the barbs but anything would help.\nWhen you get time to look at them and mail me. A\n                                  Akira\n\n**\ntats\n**\nTo: mangla\nSubj: North Carolina\nCc: airborne, sauron, haplo\nDate: Sep  5\n\n\nDon't you live in North Carolina somewhere, cause you will never\nguess where I live.\n\nLiving in Washington, NC with my fiance, working at Calvary Manufactured\nHousing, as Sales Manager.\n\nI knew you and Jewel live down here somewhere.\n\nBTW.  This is still an official attempt to reverse the clamety that lead to\nmy unwilling departure from this most excellent mud.\n\nACK, not that It is threating living in close proximity, but you can realize\nthat Tatsuo is just too incredibly cool to keep banned. Ask airborne, i \nentertain him all the time.\n\nAnyway, I thought i remembered you living in Greenville about 15 minutes from here.\nSo i said, what the hell.\n\nLater\nTatsuo\n\n**\nwilbie\n**\nTo: mangla\nSubj: Mentors\nCc: sauron, airborne, haplo\nDate: Sep 11\n\nSmorlok has asked me to be his mentor (stop laughing!).  What exactly is\nthe process?  Does he ask one of you arch-types to promote him to apprentice\nfirst, or does he ask me to ask you?  I never had a mentor...  I think you\nbanished him or something :)\n\nAnyway, he says he can code, and he's on quite a bit, and I've never heard of\nhim being a problem...\n\n**\nwilbie\n**\nTo: mangla\nSubj: Smorlok\nCc: sauron,haplo,airborne\nDate: Sep 12\n\nHe's got the age, and at Legend 20 I think he's got the experience.  Most \nimportantly (to me anyway) he seems like he wants to code some cool areas\nand help out the mud.  So I did the mentor thing.\n\nHe's coded on HM2 (don't hold that against him - a lot of us did) and he says\nhe has coded on others as well.  I am planning to be here quite a bit more,\nunless things at work get really screwed - we're replacing a mainframe\nwith an SAP/WinNT network and it's deadlined at November 2nd :)\n\nAnyway, I will help him as much as a I can, and HM has always been easy to \nget a handle on.  I think he'll make a great wizard.\n\nWilbie\n\n**\nsmorlok\n**\nTo: mangla\nSubj: mentor\nDate: Sep 12\n\nas you said, i found a mentor (wilbie) now i only need your permission to wiz\nsee ya later\n\nLD\n\n**\nakira\n**\nTo: mangla\nSubj: barbs\nDate: Sep 15\n\nSo whats the word on the barb stuff. Ya I know its crude and\nneeds some work but anything will help.\n\t\t\t\tAkira\n\n**\ngareth\n**\nTo: mangla\nSubj: mud\nDate: Sep 26\n\n\nHeya Mangs!\n\tCan you give me the low down on what's going on - or happening here?\nthanks,\n\tCarlos\n\n\n**\nbrainsprain\n**\nTo: mangla\nSubj: changes\nDate: Sep 28\n\n     I am looking to start making some changes to the thieves guild.\nIn order to do this, I need the new rooms linked into play.  \nFrom /room/sunalley2/ I need /players/brainsprain/guild/rooms/joinroom\nlinked in place of the old room going down and /players/brainsprain/guild+\n/rooms/alch_shop attached to /room/eastroad3 going east instead of the\nold alchemy shop.\n\nBrainsprain\n\n**\nbrainsprain\n**\nTo: mangla\nSubj: The file\nDate: Oct  5\n\nI haven't checked out the monster file yet, but the code makes a \nspecific TP->add_poison() call.\n\nIn any case, I will need to see the player code as well eventually,\nafter all, PK thieves may want to be able to poison enemies.\n\nThanks.\n\nBrainsprain\n**\\\n\n**\ntats\n**\nTo: mangla\nSubj: response\nCc: airborne\nDate: Oct  9\n\n\nI would very much like a positive response to my continued inquiry into being\ncompletly restored to the level i attained before a terrible mistake happened.\n\nNot only will it bring much needed activity back to the mud, but it will piss off\nExos to no end, thus making the entire idea feasible.\nExos to no end, thus making the entire idea feasible.\n\nPlease restore tatsuo completly, and soon.\n\n3 years 9 months is a little long to be away.\n\nThanks.\n\nTatsuo\n\n**\nqwerty\n**\nTo: mangla\nSubj: FTP\nDate: Oct  9\n\n\nCan you check it for me.  I dont think it is up.  At least i havent\nbeen able to connect to it.  The addr is same here but 4243 right?\n\nPlease let me know....\n\nThanks,\nMike.\n\n**\nqwerty\n**\nTo: mangla\nSubj: FTP\nDate: Oct 13\n\nany luck with herp?  I still cant get in :(\n\n**\nkryll\n**\nTo: sauron\nSubj: healing\nCc: mangla, airborne\nDate: Oct 29\n\ni do not know the current status of the docs, but i would like\nto make a suggestion about healing. i feel that the cost for\nhealing should be 4-6 gold per point it heals for static healing\n(ie. a bar or you cannot carry it around). for portable\nhealing it should be 10 times that amount (anywhere from 40-60 gold\nper hit point gained). i mention this as i check redsexy's area\nand notice a bar. comments as soon as possible would be nice.\n\nkryll\n\n**\nairborne\n**\nTo: kryll\nRe:   healing\nCc: arches\nDate: Oct 29\n\nI agree with raising the cost of healing.  I think that we should \ndo whatever we can to me the mud more challenging for players, and \nthat the abundance of healing definately has something to do with \nthat. 40-60 gold per HP for a carried is not unreasonable, however\nwe need to look at how that balances with guild regenerative abilities\nas well.  Once we limit the availability of portable healing, suddenly\nany guild that offers healing is considerably more potent.  I think if \nwe do things like this that we should perhaps balance meditation skills\nwith something like 'can only meditate in a temple'... with that being \njust one example.\n\nW.\n\n**\nsauron\n**\nTo: airborne\nRe:   healing\nCc: arches\nDate: Oct 31\n\nI don't know that we should remove all meditation outside of a 'temple' but\nmaybe we could reduce the healing rate outside of that player's guild rooms.\nSeems to me that being in their temple, or at their shrine, or whatever,\nshould heal them faster, or conversely, being away from there should heal\nthem slower (since we want to reduce the healing, not increase it).\n\nDave\n\n**\nairborne\n**\nTo: mangla\nFwd:  healing\nCc: arches\nDate: Nov  1\n\nTo: airborne\nRe:   healing\nCc: arches\nDate: Oct 31\n\nI don't know that we should remove all meditation outside of a 'temple' but\nmaybe we could reduce the healing rate outside of that player's guild rooms.\nSeems to me that being in their temple, or at their shrine, or whatever,\nshould heal them faster, or conversely, being away from there should heal\nthem slower (since we want to reduce the healing, not increase it).\n\nDave\n\n**\nairborne\n**\nTo: mangla\nSubj: healing...\nCc: arches\nDate: Nov  1\n\nSorry about that, zigged when I should have zagged.\n\nHere's the idea that I have been bouncing about in my head.  \n\nOk, suppose we limit meditation/healing skills to only the guild room\nand \"shrines\".  Then we give guild members the ability to create \nshrines in various locations.  Players will be able to have their \nhealing, but they would have to work a bit for it.  \n\nTo start, we'd have the shrine needed to be built.  An easy way to\nget players to spend a bunch of gold on all sorts of things, bowls, \nstatues, insense, etc.  Then they would have to protect those locations\nonce they were built.  Certainly leaving lots of valuables laying \naround would tempt almost any player, which would kinda be the point.\nAdd in the idea that some elements of theshrine would degrade with\ntime (insence comes to mind) and have to be replaced every so \noften.  \n\nThe idea is to create an economy by finding reasons for players to gather\nor purchase things that aren't just for killing.  If insence were only\navailable in a small handful of locations, and there was a demand for it\nwe'd create the demand.  It helps control healing rates, keeps money\ndown a bit, adds a roleplaying element to the mud, and encourages guilds\nto work together.\n\nIdeas and critics?\n\n\n**\ntatsuo\n**\nTo: mangla\nSubj: reopen ezo and ishikawa\nCc: wilbie, airborne\nDate: Nov  3\n\n\nWilbie and I would like to reopen at least the areas of ezo and ishikawa, the area\ncoded by patience, that i recoded, and the area, haplo and I, (secret: I coded whole \nthing),  coded with the ishikawa quest.\n\npriorities for project.\n\n1. Get Ezo reopened save for the ninja guild halls, upgrade monsters, and equipment\n  to current standards.\n\n2. Reopen Ishikawa, reinstate quest, recode as necessary.\n\n3. Reopen Ninja guild, I believe i have the talent and experience necessary after\n   completion of first two steps to get it working.  Wilbie as well.\n\n4.  Recode and reopen of samurai guild. \n\n\nThese eastern areas were a HUGE attraction in during the old days, and wilbie and\nmyself remember enough of it, having been part, and coding extensivly with these areas.\n\nPlease approve the project, and give instructions for implementation of each part.\n\nTatsuo & Wilbie\n\n**\nwilbie\n**\nTo: tatsuo\nSubj: Ezo etc\nCc: mangla\nDate: Nov  3\n\nAs far as I know, Ezo is completely open and complete.  Warlord has the ninja\nguild coming slowly but surely.  I have been doing some weapons for my \nFuzhou area that are ninja compatable (was working with Darastor on that).\nBecause we are implementing SAP here at work, I haven't done much but we're\nnow done implementing, so I will be coding a lot more now.\n\nAs far as Samurai/Ishikawa go, I will help out with whatever.  Actually, you\ncan put Fuzhou in Ishikawa.  It's a small fishing village.\n\n**\ntatsuo\n**\nTo: mangla\nSubj: more stuff, with some facts this time\nDate: Feb  4\n\n\n\n\nAdditional Ideas and proposals for Holy Mission, Displayed in Non marketed format.\n\n\n1.  Allow force command for Sage or Lord levels to assist players without\n    having to dictate every action necessary.\n    \n    Example.  Player bob has problem with spell not working, upon\n    snooping Eldr wiz believes it to be alias problem instead of asking\n    player to type alias, or nickname, the force command would save time\n    and bickering from spammy players!  Also allows forced saves, etc.\n   \n    Fact.  Every other mud i have experienced allows this at midlevels\n\n2.  Wizlist,  I believe the list_wiz function is still in the master object.\n    I have all these print outs from the period in which i was an archwizard.\n    The sad part is that i actually kept them in a box.  This could be\n    interesting command for wizards to see who else is a wizard and I \n    never understood why it was reserved for the wiz levels,  if there\n    is a reason, enlighten me.\n\n3.  Can we officially appoint GM's, and ask around or post for GM's to \n    take over for inactives.  Even inexperienced ones would be beneficial\n    as there are some coders around to assist them now.  Some names come\n    to mind.  Waldo, Wilbie, Bobo.\n\n4.  I would like to place an idea board in the elevator room just west\n    of church.  I would also like to place a sign in the description of\n    the church that when read reveals the location, directions to, description\n    of the various newbie areas, as well as indicating the newbie should\n    explore the knowledge in 'help newbie'  The idea board would specifically\n    address ideas to be added, changed, deleted from the game from players.\n    Wizards willing to take up the challenge could post their interest in\n    coding the idea in response.  Once ideas get posted, then other players\n    usually draw on the idea, and when players log in and see that ideas\n    are actually being taken care of quickly, they may want to try them, and\n    may stick around more than the average 2 minute login to check mail, and\n    say HI.\n\n5.  Would like endorsement of the clan system, so i can standardize and establish\n    creation rules,  It is VERY popular, there are now 4 clans role playing\n    different groups.  Each is sponsered by [WIZ] or higher.  The code\n    is available to any who want it as are all my files.\n\n    Tatsuo - Wing Cong -  Oriental Assassins and spies\n    Waldo- Lycanthropes - Psuedo shape changers (titles and short desc only)\n    Bobo-  Heiliolites - Fanatically pagan sun worshipers!\n    Wilbie - Inquisitors - MORE fanatics!  Group of evil wannabes.\n    Several other wizards including Sargon have voiced interest in starting\n    a clan.\n\n    Clans have NO benefit to the players attributes,  only neat emotes, chat line,\n    title sets, a pose, and common areas hidden in the mud, perhaps with a board.\n    This unites players, and rivalries are friendly.  The Clanmaster must make\n    it clear that Pking in the name of the clan is forbidden because of the\n    last great 'Clan war'.  \n\n    The guilds provide abilites for players, the Clan provides the personality \n    of the character.  Hopefully more wizards will have better ideas.\n\n6.  Bobo has done an excellent job in redesigning Kellie's area, this area\n    is ready for final inspect and installation.  It is very near your\n    area and you would be more familiar with it than I.  It is 99% bug free, as\n    I might have missed something.\n\n7.  In case you are wondering why this not is so damn long, I am doing it on notepad\n    on a stupid 386, at work.  It is 4am and I am training this dumbass kid\n    how to audit.  He is pretty much doing it on his own, So i am a babysitter for\n    the rest of the week.  So I decided to bother our esteemed arch staff.\n\n8.  From what i can tell, the summoner code has been deemed inefficient \n    because each creature is using call_outs and hearbeats every tick of its\n    existance.  This does not seem to be a problem as I checked the active\n    heartbeats on the mud for the last several days, and found that a consistant\n    15 to 20 obj/monsters are active at any time.  There will never be more\n    than 2 or 3 summoners on at any time, thus increasing this number by\n    6 to 9 hbs.   It looks a hell of alot more efficient than that damn \n    mage guild shadow that has been around since llort first threw it together.\n    Did you know every mage staff carrys a heartbeat to restore the hp/sp of\n    the player?\n\n    I am trying to get some facts for the reinstallation of summoner guild.\n    Again, correct me if I am wrong.  Also as much as you correct me for\n    speaking for Wilbie,  I know for a fact he would like running the \n    Summoner guild.  I wish Matt was still around and arched to keep it in the\n    game!  \n\n9.  Another area ready for final inspect is a newbie area that I coded\n    myself,  The first 1/2 of the area, the halfling part is complete and\n    located in /players/tatsuo/halfling.  It will link up nicely with\n    the oppressing kobold area, the area contains a newbie level 3 star \n    quest.  I will have the kobold area working in less than a week.\n    At about the same time Ishikawa will reopen with inspection as\n    one of those ULTRA high level areas,  It is far off and difficult to\n    get to.   Thumper also has an area approaching approval quickly, i will\n    advise when its ready for final inspect.  Bobo has commenced an area\n    with the same theme as his clan.\n\n10.  You were right about Exos being pissed.  At first he declared to \n     the masses that he was quitting HM.  This was soon changed to his\n     badmouthing me at every chance, publically.  I have not snooped, \n     interfered with or lied about him to anyone during this period.\n     Last night his chastising included talking publically about \n     opening a munchkin/midget infested area.  This offends two fold\n     He knows that I myself am terrified of midgets (blush), its\n     irrational, but Turbo knows me and told exos about it.  Secondly\n     and more offensive is Airbornes reaction if he happened to log\n     on during this.   I don't give a shit about him talking about it.\n     (but if a midget walked in the door, i would be out the back door!)\n     He is just being very bitter, and does not contribute,  He was again\n     very pissed 4 days ago when players asked me for help rather than\n     him and ignored him when he showed up to help.  ( it was an alias \n     problem with the single alias bug)  He doesn't contribute he\n     just uses that tongue of his as poison.  Do what you will.  I make\n     no suggestions.  I personally dispise him because of his multiple\n     sexual harassment episodes that i know are factual.\n\nThat about wraps up everything I can think of at the moment.  I believe that\nwe need some short term fixes that are easy to implement before we start \naddressing the long term problems.\n\nOh yeah.\n\n11.  When can we kick up to 3 to 5 day reboot.\n     Hope you can do it asap.\n\nTatsuo\n\n\n**\ntatsuo\n**\nTo: mangla\nSubj: redsexy\nDate: Mar  6\n\n\nQC complete\nWas excellent\n\nYou don't even need to go through it. I certify it 100%\nread mentor board for specifics\nTats\n\n**\ntatsuo\n**\nTo: mangla\nSubj: bobo\nDate: Mar  6\n\nBobo revamped almost all of ezo.\ncleaning up bad english and typos.\nTats\n\n**\nsargon\n**\nTo: mangla\nSubj: mobs\nDate: Mar  6\n\nIn Turbo's area....a thing called a Kosh....these are the stats:\n-----------------------------------------------------\nLevel : 1000 (0)        Experience     : 1141   Align : 0\nCoins : 0       Carried weight : 0(1010)\nHP    : 1508042         of 1508042\nSP    : 1508042         of 1508042\nStr   : 1000 (1000)  Dex: 1000 (1000)  Con: 1000 (1000)\nInt   : 1000 (1000)  Wis: 1000 (1000)  Chr: 1000 (1000)\n-----------------------------------------------------\nRanking: Mortal\nGuild         : 0 adventurer\nArmourclass   : 100   natural: 100\n----- Armours -----\n-------------------\nMore? [q to quit]\n---hands---\nNatural WC    : 201\nMore? [q to quit]\nnumber of arms: 1\nnothing holdingBrings me to deaths door in one hit.\nWhy on earth do we need a mob that is that powerful?\nIt seems to me that this will escalate guild powers so that\nmobs like this can be killed....is there a special object\nneeded to kill this?\n\nSargon\n\n**\ntatsuo\n**\nTo: mangla\nSubj: summonre\nCc: redsexy, wilbie\nDate: Mar  7\n\nI found the file that could possibly crash the mud in the summoners\nIt can be easily removed\nscontrol.c in the obj dir\nremoving the seeker is no big deal\nI can't find any other reason to to reopen the guild.\nI will bin it up and remove the seeker, and that should be good to go\nRedsexy or wilbie have bothed voiced interest in running that guild.\n\n2.\nBarb guild moved back to original location.\n\n3.  Conan moved near campfire, is valid mob\n\n4.  You should move your jedi guild inside redsexy's area. it rocks and\nis very jedi theme\nperhaps mos eisley\n\n5. have a nice day.\n\n**\nredsexy\n**\nTo: mangla\nSubj: Jedi Guild in my Area\nDate: Mar  7\n\nHi,  I've just been thinking on this and because of the lag\nthink this is the best way to outline my idea.\n\nI think the Jedi Guild would be ideally situated near the\nport town of the island of Carkoon.  That way the portal\nwould still come in handy (it would save the jedi a\nboat ride and a trip across the desert).\n\nI will set about modifying a test file now linking to\nthe guild from the island and then talk to you about it,\nlag permitting :-)!\n\nFive minutes :-)\n\nRedsexy\n\n**\nsargon\n**\nTo: mangla\nSubj: Fighter\nDate: Mar  8\n\nHi,\nI'd like to GM fighter.  If its acceptable i'd like to have write access to\nit somehow.  Or move it to my dir.  Please let me know.\nThanks\n\nSargon\n\n**\nuruz\n**\nTo: mangla\nSubj: da wiz\nDate: Mar  9\n\nTrout here,\nJust checking in to see if you decided you wanted to let me wiz under this\ncharacter, Uruz. Keep me appraised.\n\nKeep the faith,\nTrout\n\n**\nredsexy\n**\nTo: mangla\nSubj: Idea...\nDate: Mar  9\n\nHi Mangla,\n\n\nI'm feeling in a Tatsuo mood!  THIS IS WHAT I WANT DONE NOW!!!!!!!!!!\n\nI want wizards to be able to help newbies.  Yes, actually take them killing\nshow them the MUD, tell them information and directions they may\notherwise not find out, get them get items.\n\nFAILIURE TO COMPLY WITH THIS WILL RESULT IN ME LEAVING\nTHE MUD FOREVER AND EVER AND EVER AND EVER AND SULKING\nEVERY TIME YOUR NAME IS MENTIONED!!!!!!\n\nOhhh laugh out loud.\n\nSeriously though, I think if there's only a clueless newbie and a wiz\nthe rules on interaction can afford to be relaxed a little.  The two \noptions are you give them basic directions and hope they find some\nweapons or something or you log off your wiz character and come\non with your player character and hope they don't associate the two.\nIt may sound like an alien concept, but there are people who don't\nknow that \"n\" is an abbreviation for \"north\".  I came in on this\nguy having a conversation with the Paperboy.\n\nIn my opinion (and I'm not suggesting this as a \"norm\", I'm a very\nlenient person anyway...) there is no harm in a wiz helping a newbie\nget up to level 5, provided there's no cloning of weapons, no\ngiving away of money (even then, what's the harm in 1000 coins?)\nand no quest hints invovled.  If anything, having a wiz help \na newbie SHOULD turn them into a good player.\n(get them into the habit of examining things in rooms, etc.).\nOK, we should be concentrating on coding or something wizlike.\nBut what's the point in coding if no-one's gonna be around to\nenjoy the code.\n\nOther stuff?  Ohhh there's plenty of other stuff, trust me :-)\nBut it can wait.\n\nIf you're dead set against this idea, I understand why.\nIt goes against everything we've ever been taught about\nwizplayer interaction.\n\nIf not then congratulations!\n\nYou've just had a \"playerkeeping\" idea!\n\nGet it implemented!\n\nDo it unexpectedly!\n\nWatch everyone run around in \ncircles of confusion!\n\nYour mentee,\n\nRedsexy\n\nPS I've also made some brief posts about the MUD on various sites\nand bulletin boards.  I've noticed a LOT more newbies today.\nThis is what we're aiming for, yes?\n\n**\nmangla\n**\nTo: tatsuo\nSubj: ezo coast\nCc: arches\nDate: Mar  9\n\nI had to fix up players/tatsuo/ezo/coast/genCoast.c\nthis morning. This is the second day in a row that\nareas of Ezo would not load. Please be more careful when\nchanging things. All errors are simple. Missing ;\nor extra \" and in this case one of the problems was\na function redefinition.\n\n-Mangla\n\n**\nturbo\n**\nTo: mangla\nSubj: /p/turbo/obj/raise_rod.c\nDate: Mar  9\n\nIs this illegal?  \nIF 'yes' then {\nIs there a way to make it legal?}\nELSE\n{ can I add it into the game?  since it requires two people, it should be balanced }\n\n**\nredsexy\n**\nTo: mangla\nSubj: Question.\nDate: Mar  9\n\nHas the newbie map in the map room ben updated lately?\nJust wondering, if not I can work on it tonight.\n\nRed\n\n**\nredsexy\n**\nTo: mangla\nSubj: Disregard!\nDate: Mar  9\n\nOK I checked out the directions - just some confusion from\na newbie who took the three sets of directions\nin a row to be one set of directions :-) :-)\n\n*chuckle*\n\nlaters :-)\n\n**\ntatsuo\n**\nTo: mangla\nSubj: ezo\nDate: Mar  9\n\nbobo is redoing ezo\n\n**\ndarastor\n**\nTo: mangla\nSubj: location command\nCc: darastor\nDate: Mar  9\n\nThe code for the command is in /p/d/sys/bin/location.c\nI tried using parse_command but couldn't get it working the way\nI really wanted it to so he code there is what I fell back on.\nThe command syntax is \"location <town> <state>, <country>\"\n\nTest it out then put it in place 